article.headline: Sacramento State 64, UC Irvine 56
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Brandon Guyton hit scored all 12 of his points on 3-pointers to help Sacramento State snap a four-game losing streak with a 64-56 win over UC Irvine on Saturday night. Joseth Dawson added 10 points for Sacramento State (4-5), making all eight of his free throws as the Hornets held off a late rally by the Anteaters (5-4). Mike Efevberha had 11 points, and Adam Parada added seven points and 15 rebounds for the Anteaters, who shot less than 32 percent and made 20 turnovers to lose despite outrebounding Sacramento State 43-31.
